45:13.403 --> 45:21.394
I mean, obviously, the fact that they met up implies some kind of link, and all sorts of circumstantial links within the intelligence service.

45:21.414 --> 45:25.600
You know what's a telling detail to me, and what I hadn't realized, is that they weren't in a tavern.

45:26.221 --> 45:31.849
I mean, this was not just some kind of idle day in a bar, you know what I mean?

45:31.949 --> 45:32.951
That's right.

45:33.171 --> 45:35.254
That's a pretty interesting point to me.

45:35.435 --> 45:53.241
Part of the disinformation, I mean, whether it's intended disinformation or whether it's just sort of the way that rumors and hearsays work, but the idea that it was a tavern all sort of changes the nature of the thing so radically, and one gets back behind that idea that

45:53.828 --> 45:57.772
I think, yeah, as you say, it makes it a whole different story.

45:58.373 --> 46:01.757
And, you know, one could regard that as, to some extent, a cover-up.

46:01.837 --> 46:09.866
You know, the fact that everyone seems to think it was a tavern ball sort of almost... Spontaneous, but it doesn't seem to be that at all.

46:11.167 --> 46:22.840
And, in fact, that he's killed long after the bill was, you know, I mean, it wasn't like where we're arguing over the checks on the table, you know, we're saying, anti-up, you know, that's not how it happened.

46:23.174 --> 46:30.929
Yes, I mean, they've been together for at least seven to ten hours.

46:31.089 --> 46:33.213
Well, they've been, no, at least eight hours.

46:33.293 --> 46:33.734
Sure.

46:33.754 --> 46:41.268
Because they meet at ten and they go for supper at six or eight hours, and then the killing happens unspecified for the time after that.

46:41.709 --> 46:43.933
So it's, yeah, I mean, there's...

46:44.251 --> 46:47.154
It's not just a, yeah, it's not just a quick drink together.

46:47.174 --> 46:55.043
Wouldn't it be wonderful if there were some newspapers, you know, you could go to the morgue, you know, what we call them, pull the clips on the stuff.

46:55.063 --> 46:56.184
Well, it's a double-edged thing, of course.

46:56.204 --> 47:04.413
Once you've committed your theories to print, you're kind of dreading the sudden discovery of another bit of paper.

47:04.453 --> 47:10.439
Yeah, the coroner's report is really maddening, too, isn't it, for what it doesn't tell you?

47:10.800 --> 47:11.220
Yes.

47:12.415 --> 47:18.000
I mean, I don't sort of go down the line that the coroner's report is in itself a kind of cover-up.

47:18.020 --> 47:19.342
I mean, people have said this.

47:19.562 --> 47:24.547
As we've said earlier, I'm not the first conspiracy theorist by any means.

47:26.829 --> 47:35.918
People have certainly sort of suggested that, you know, this whole coroner's inquest was a deliberate cover-up in itself.

47:36.438 --> 47:38.420
I don't myself see it that way.

47:38.440 --> 47:41.123
I think it was a perfectly straight-up piece of

47:41.558 --> 47:46.223
He was added to determine cause of death, I guess that's about it.

47:46.564 --> 47:52.270
Yes, I mean, I think the cover-up is a question of what the witnesses told the coroner.

47:53.552 --> 47:55.814
Why is the price of the dagger such a big deal?

47:55.834 --> 48:07.127
I think I'm right in saying that it's something that's often mentioned in these coroner's reports because

48:07.681 --> 48:13.291
the murder weapon became the sort of property or was confiscated as the property.

48:13.311 --> 48:14.132
Oh, I see.

48:14.192 --> 48:26.213
Therefore, the value of it was actually a sort of, you know, equivalent to the sort of polythene bag around the suspected controlled substances.

48:26.767 --> 48:32.013
You know, it's a purely, I think, I'm right in saying, a purely administrative detail.

48:32.493 --> 48:44.466
It might be also an idea that a 12-penny dagger tells us or told someone then what kind of dagger it was, you know, whether a 12-penny dagger was probably considered to be a certain size.

48:46.028 --> 48:52.555
But it's, I don't think there's much that one can

48:53.902 --> 48:55.064
discerned from it now.

48:55.164 --> 48:59.590
It just always strikes me as a rather nice detail that it was a 12-penny dagger.

48:59.610 --> 49:04.838
Of course, that's actually not by any means a cheap dagger, which is what I might think that is.

49:04.878 --> 49:11.748
12 pence is actually, as I reckon, it's probably about 25 quid.

